# Cursor rules for NextAPI monorepo

## Non-negotiable
1. Always read CLAUDE.md before any architectural decision.
2. New module = start by writing docs/modules/<name>.md.
3. Every new backend function gets a test.
4. Frontend: shadcn conventions, no custom CSS unless necessary.

## Code style
- Go: small packages, explicit errors with codes, context.Context as first arg.
- TypeScript: strict mode, no any, functional components, Server Components by default.
- SQL: snake_case tables (plural), all changes via goose migrations.
- HTTP: /v1/ prefix, plural resources, standard HTTP codes.

## Security
- Never hardcode secrets. Use .env.
- Always validate input in handlers.
- Use parametrized queries (GORM/sqlc). Never string-concat SQL.
- Rate limit per api_key AND per IP on /v1/*.

## Internationalization
- All user-facing copy goes through next-intl.
- Keys live in apps/{app}/messages/{en,zh}.json.
- English first, Chinese fills second.

## Forbidden
- Creating templates/workflows (was scrapped design).
- Adding providers beyond Seedance in v1.
- Using `any` or `interface{}` without a TODO comment.
- Inline CSS in React components.
- Committing .env, keys, or any secret.
